278
00:14:52,780 --> 00:14:54,780
Because during dinner,

279
00:14:54,780 --> 00:14:57,980
Haruna mentioned that the music box played Haru yo Koi

280
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,280
and since it was your grandmother's favorite song

281
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:03,080
and she always played it on the koto,

282
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:09,880
you thought the stamps just might be hidden inside the koto.

283
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:13,880
But even if the koto dropped down from the ceiling,

284
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,680
I don't see how it could have knocked him unconscious,

285
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:18,880
there wasn't enough momentum.

286
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:21,380
Besides, if he was going to look inside the koto,

287
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:23,580
wouldn't he have turned the lights on?

288
00:15:23,580 --> 00:15:28,680
When we got there, the room was dark, wasn't it?

289
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:33,580
Minoru didn't not turn the lights on, he couldn't.

290
00:15:33,580 --> 00:15:36,080
The device the culprit rigged raised the light up,

291
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,180
close to the ceiling and in the dark,

292
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:43,980
Minoru didn't know where the light cord was,

293
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:45,480
left with no other choice,

294
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,180
Minoru got down on the floor

295
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:48,580
and felt around the area the koto usually is,

296
00:15:48,580 --> 00:15:50,980
when he found it, he intended to take it to his room.

297
00:15:50,980 --> 00:15:53,680
Then he heard the sound of the string

298
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:57,180
rubbing against the fishing line and he looked up,

299
00:15:57,180 --> 00:16:00,080
and of all the bad luck, that's when it fell on his head.

300
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:02,680
Minoru.

301
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:05,480
Okay, so you're right, you've got me.

302
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:09,480
But how was it rigged to drop the koto, anyway?

303
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,780
It's very simple.

304
00:16:11,780 --> 00:16:15,680
First, you get one very long fishing line

305
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:19,580
wrap the light cord around the middle of the fishing line,

306
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:22,780
then pass both ends of the line under the string,

307
00:16:22,780 --> 00:16:26,780
the koto is then probably temporarily placed on the chest.

308
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:29,780
Next, both ends of the line is passed through the transom

309
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:31,180
and went through Shiro's room, then Minoru's

310
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:33,680
and then Mr. and Mrs. Ogata's

311
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:35,680
until finally reaching the room Ran and Haruna were staying in.

312
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:38,480
Then, so the line wouldn't sag, both ends were tied

313
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:42,080
then set in place between the doors with a hair pin.

314
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:44,080
Next, take the koto off the chest and let it hang,

315
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:46,380
then your booby trap is complete.

316
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:49,880
After that, all you had to do was open the door...

317
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,080
The hair pin would be released

318
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,880
and that would lead to the koto falling.

319
00:16:56,880 --> 00:17:00,380
Now wait just one minute, you're not saying that...

320
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:01,580
That's right.

321
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:03,680
The person responsible for tonight's ghostly apparition

322
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:06,780
is the person who opened that door.

323
00:17:06,780 --> 00:17:08,680
Kazuko.

324
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,680
It was you, wasn't it?

325
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,180
Mother?

326
00:17:13,180 --> 00:17:14,580
But why?

327
00:17:14,580 --> 00:17:15,580
It's probably because

328
00:17:15,580 --> 00:17:20,080
she didn't want Haruna to go looking for those stamps.

329
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:25,280
I'm pretty sure she rigged the booby trap while we were eating,

330
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:28,280
when she left to go prepare our bedding.

331
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:32,180
Then when she heard Ran and Haruna scream,

332
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:35,780
she came running and opened the door nonchalantly,

333
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:37,080
causing the koto to fall.

334
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:40,680
And then, while everyone was rushing to Shugo's room,

335
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,980
she removed the cut out from the window

336
00:17:42,980 --> 00:17:46,980
and sent a message to Haruna's pocket bell from her cellular,

337
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:49,080
trying to scare her.

338
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,080
"I was waiting for you, Haruna"

339
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:54,980
She was trying to frighten Haruna away from this house.

340
00:17:54,980 --> 00:18:00,580
But what did she do with all that fishing line after that?

341
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:04,880
Mom was right behind us when we got to grandfather's room.

342
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,380
She didn't have time to take the paper off the window

343
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:10,380
and remove all the fishing line while using the telephone.

344
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,780
She had a very handy helper.

345
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:16,380
It's right behind Ran.

346
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:18,680
A fan?

347
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:21,280
I'm pretty sure she cut the tied end of the line

348
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:27,380
and pulled one end into this room then used tape to tape it.

349
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:30,980
To the back of this fans blade.

350
00:18:32,580 --> 00:18:33,980
I see.

351
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,580
All she had to do was turn the switch on

352
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:40,080
and it would automatically reel the line in.

353
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:41,980
I still can't believe it though.

354
00:18:41,980 --> 00:18:43,380
How could you think of such a thing

355
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:47,180
in the short time you had during dinner?

356
00:18:47,180 --> 00:18:48,580
It's not impossible.

357
00:18:48,580 --> 00:18:50,680
After all, this trick with the fishing line,

358
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:53,380
is something I picked up from the pranks the boys used to pull

359
00:18:53,380 --> 00:18:55,080
when they were children.

360
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:57,280
What about the cut out of the old man?

361
00:18:57,280 --> 00:19:01,080
Oh, that, a guest who stayed with us once

362
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:04,780
thought some leaves stuck to the window was someone's shadow,

363
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:06,380
I remembered that.

364
00:19:06,380 --> 00:19:09,480
Haruna scared me.

365
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:11,180
She mentioned she collected stamps

366
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:13,780
and she said she wanted to visit us again.

367
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:18,480
Were you the one who sent me the messages before saying, 'Thief'?

368
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,480
Yes, that was me. I'm sorry.

369
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,680
Mother, that was terrible.

370
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:26,980
How could you break grandmothers koto over a thing like that?

371
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:30,480
Oh, that koto isn't worth anything.

372
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:32,180
-How can you say that? -The truth is,

373
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:37,280
I pawned the real koto and got a cheap replacement.

374
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:41,280
My new system kitchen, your new car,

375
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,280
Minoru's computer,

376
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:46,780
we were so far in debt.

377
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:49,180
Then I guess we'll just have to sell

378
00:19:49,180 --> 00:19:50,780
the music box grandfather gave me.

379
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:53,780
Oh, but I had it looked at and I was told

380
00:19:53,780 --> 00:19:56,780
it was just an ordinary souvenir item.

381
00:19:56,780 --> 00:19:57,880
That's strange.

382
00:19:57,880 --> 00:20:00,280
Grandfather told me that

383
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,880
in appreciation of my posing to be him,

384
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,380
he was giving me his music box,

385
00:20:04,380 --> 00:20:05,880
those who knew what they were looking at

386
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,780
would realize it was worth 200 million.

387
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:11,680
200 million? That music box?

388
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:16,680
Dad bought that as a souvenir when he went to a hot spring.

389
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:19,480
Grandpa pulled a fast one on you.

390
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:22,380
The music box itself isn't worth anything,

391
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:24,980
it's the missing notes.

